## 🔬 Methodology

### 1. Data Collection
- Collected real-time **vibration** and **temperature** readings from IoT sensors mounted on AC exhaust fans
- Streamed data to cloud for storage and processing

### 2. Data Cleaning & EDA
- Handled missing values, outliers, and noise in sensor readings
- Conducted EDA to identify failure patterns and correlations

### 3. Feature Extraction
- Applied **Fast Fourier Transform (FFT)** to extract frequency-domain features from vibration signals
- Engineered statistical features: mean, std, RMS, peak amplitude

### 4. Model Training
| Model | Accuracy |
|---|---|
| Support Vector Machine (SVM) | ~92% |
| Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) | ~93% |
| **Random Forest** | **~95% ✅** |

### 5. Deployment
- Deployed best model to a **cloud-based real-time monitoring dashboard**
- Automated alerts triggered on anomaly detection
- Generated maintenance reports for the engineering team

